title: Runtime Error: Cannot compile QRC on M1 Mac
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

Hello,
I have installed the DEEPLABCUT_M1 conda environment on M1 Mac running Monterey 12.6.

I am able to open the GUI, create a new project, load videos and extract frames. However, when I attempt to label data the program crashes. This occurs both from the GUI as well as direct from code.

It appears to be an issue with compiling QRC.

### Operating System

M1 Mac running Monterey 12.6.

### DeepLabCut version

2.3rc2

### DeepLabCut mode

single animal

### Device type

gpu

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Open terminal
2. `conda activate DEEPLABCUT_M1`
3. `ipython`
4. `import deeplabcut`
5. `path_config = 'path-to-project/config.yaml'`
6. `deeplabcut.label_frames(path_config)`

### Relevant log output

```shell
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
RuntimeError                              Traceback (most recent call last)
Cell In [3], line 1
----> 1 deeplabcut.label_frames(path_config)

----> 9     _ = launch_napari(config_path)

     27 def launch_napari(files=None):
---> 28     viewer = napari.Viewer()

     30     for action in viewer.window.plugins_menu.actions():

     57 # having this import here makes all of Qt imported lazily, upon
     58 # instantiating the first Viewer.

---> 61 self._window = Window(self, show=show)
     62 self._instances.add(self)
```
